00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:24,000
Do you have a watch or something?

269
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:35,000
Aren't you hungry?

270
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:37,000
My sister ate all the bread herself.

271
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:40,000
Did you really go ask everyone?

272
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:44,000
This is it?!

273
00:39:44,000 --> 00:39:48,000
I told you that's all!

274
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:53,000
It's true. Yesterday I met someone
in the vacant room.

275
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:01,000
She said they got her
while she was out jogging last night.

276
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:09,000
Then... it's one day for her today.

277
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:13,000
It's been three days for you and me.

278
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:17,000
For the college student, it's been two days.

279
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:23,000
The girl in this room said
she's been here for six days already.

280
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:31,000
The girl in that room...

281
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:33,000
...has gone.

282
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:36,000
Gone?

283
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:40,000
Mhm. Wonder if she's gone outside...

284
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:12,000
This is the girl in the room furthest from ours!

285
00:43:35,000 --> 00:43:38,000
Why's this happening?!

286
00:43:38,000 --> 00:43:42,000
Why?!

287
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:06,000
Every day,
he comes to attack the next one in line.

288
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:08,000
The one who was locked up six days ago.

289
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:12,000
At 6 o'clock, he chops them up.

290
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:16,000
I'm sure he never takes a day off.

291
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:21,000
Like toothbrushing,
it has to be done everyday.

292
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:25,000
He won't kill you will he?

293
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:29,000
You'll probably escape, and live a long life.

294
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:34,000
I'm jealous.

295
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:38,000
If it was your turn today,
would you want to know about it?

296
00:44:39,000 --> 00:44:43,000
What if it were you, sis?
Would you want to know?

297
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:42,000
Great, you came!

298
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:45,000
Your sister can use this if she likes.

299
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:48,000
Are you sure?

300
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:52,000
I won't be needing it anymore.

301
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:59,000
But...

302
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:04,000
Why are we being killed?

303
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:08,000
I don't know!

304
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:28,000
Warm, aren't you...

305
00:46:57,000 --> 00:47:00,000
Someone's coming.
He'll find me!

306
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:03,000
He's coming to kill me!

307
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:07,000
I don't want to die alone!

308
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:11,000
No, no, no...

309
00:48:21,000 --> 00:48:25,000
Satoshi!

310
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:31,000
Shit!!

311
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:36,000
I thought he'd killed you too.

312
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:57,000
What kind of person was it?

313
00:48:57,000 --> 00:49:01,000
I couldn't see his face.

314
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:04,000
But it was a huge guy.

315
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:08,000
If we attack him together,
don't you think we could win?

316
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:14,000
He has a chainsaw.

317
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:24,000
The door, it seems it has a pole lock.

318
00:49:27,000 --> 00:49:31,000
It sounded that way when he opened it!

319
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:36,000
So that means doesn't lock with a key?

320
00:50:26,000 --> 00:50:30,000
Don't come any closer!
I won't let you hurt my little brother!

321
00:50:50,000 --> 00:50:54,000
Satochi!

322
00:51:02,000 --> 00:51:05,000
After he comes here,
he'll try to kill us right away.

323
00:51:05,000 --> 00:51:09,000
But, he won't know you'll leave the room.

324
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:13,000
You'll go and let everyone out.

325
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:16,000
If you enter that way,
I'm sure everyone will understand.

326
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:20,000
But what about you, sis?

327
00:51:55,000 --> 00:51:59,000
This way!

328
00:52:00,000 --> 00:52:02,000
Let's go!

329
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:06,000
Hurry up!

330
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:58,000
I want to go home real soon.

331
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:02,000
When we get home, please take a bath.
You seriously stink.

332
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:14,000
What did you think when I was born?

333
00:53:15,000 --> 00:53:20,500
What's this? Honestly, I didn't feel
there was any connection between us.

334
00:53:53,000 --> 00:53:57,000
Sis...

335
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:13,000
Let's go call the police.

336
00:56:31,000 --> 00:56:35,000
"3 people were seriously injured..."

337
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:40,000
"...traffic accident..."

338
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:07,000
When did you get back?

339
00:57:07,000 --> 00:57:11,000
Want me to give you a hand with that?

340
00:57:12,000 --> 00:57:16,000
I'm OK.

341
00:57:16,000 --> 00:57:19,000
I see.

342
00:57:19,000 --> 00:57:23,000
Keep at it.

343
00:57:23,000 --> 00:57:27,000
You're just drinking juice again?

344
00:57:30,000 --> 00:57:31,000
No homework?

345
00:57:31,000 --> 00:57:35,000
Yeah. But dad told me to
keep working on my puzzle.

346
00:57:40,000 --> 00:57:43,000
Your dad isn't here, is he?

347
00:57:43,000 --> 00:57:47,000
Huh?

348
00:57:47,000 --> 00:57:51,000
So for my sake,
please do your homework.

349
00:57:56,000 --> 00:58:00,000
Alright.

350
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:07,000
If you do your homework over there,
you'll ruin your eyes.

351
00:58:08,000 --> 00:58:12,000
Now, let's go get something sweet to eat.

352
00:58:21,000 --> 00:58:25,000
Hey... what about mom?

353
00:58:38,000 --> 00:58:42,000
From that day on,
dad wasn't able to see mom.

354
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:48,000
And mom wasn't able to see dad.

355
00:58:56,000 --> 00:58:58,000
Ah!

356
00:58:58,000 --> 00:59:02,000
It's dad.

357
00:59:08,000 --> 00:59:12,000
I know it's painful but...
your dad is gone.

358
00:59:14,000 --> 00:59:18,000
From now on, it's just the two of us.

359
00:59:18,000 --> 00:59:22,000
Let's do our best, OK?

360
00:59:39,000 --> 00:59:43,000
Hey! Which boxed dinner would you like?

361
00:59:59,000 --> 01:00:03,000
Do you remember that day your dad
and I went out in the car?

362
01:00:10,000 --> 01:00:14,000
Your dad was driving,
when an accident happened.

363
01:00:18,000 --> 01:00:22,000
In the end...

364
01:00:23,000 --> 01:00:27,000
only I was saved.

365
01:00:32,000 --> 01:00:36,000
Your mom and I went over to your uncle's house.

366
01:00:39,000 --> 01:00:43,000
And after that, we were in a car accident.

367
01:00:48,000 --> 01:00:52,000
I was safe...
but your mother...

368
01:01:10,000 --> 01:01:14,000
Hey... where have the scissors gone?

369
01:01:19,000 --> 01:01:23,000
Want me to ask dad?

370
01:01:29,000 --> 01:01:33,000
Hey dad, where are the scissors?

371
01:01:35,000 --> 01:01:39,000
In a kitchen drawer, aren't they?

372
01:01:41,000 --> 01:01:45,000
He said they're in a kitchen drawer.

373
01:02:16,000 --> 01:02:20,000
I can see dad!

374
01:02:23,000 --> 01:02:26,000
Mom is right here!

375
01:02:26,000 --> 01:02:30,000
So it's not just you and me, dad.

376
01:02:33,000 --> 01:02:37,000
If there's anything you want her to know,
I'll tell her for you, OK?

377
01:02:40,000 --> 01:02:44,000
You can, can't you?
It really seems that way.

378
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:59,000
I don't know what she's talking about.

379
01:02:59,000 --> 01:03:03,000
Ask her when that happened.

380
01:03:05,000 --> 01:03:09,000
He wants to know when that happened.

381
01:03:10,000 --> 01:03:13,000
All the time.

382
01:03:13,000 --> 01:03:17,000
He doesn't say it, but he's always thinking it.

383
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:24,000
All the time, she says.
Mom looks sad.

384
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:30,000
I'm more sad than she is.

385
01:03:30,000 --> 01:03:34,000
Face reality a bit more, will you.

386
01:03:41,000 --> 01:03:45,000
Boring, isn't it?

387
01:03:47,000 --> 01:03:51,000
Mom went into the bedroom.
Is that OK?

388
01:03:56,000 --> 01:04:00,000
Leave me alone.

389
01:04:06,000 --> 01:04:10,000
Well... go tell your mom

390
01:04:17,000 --> 01:04:21,000
"I'm really glad you're not around anymore".

391
01:04:49,000 --> 01:04:53,000
What did your dad say?

392
01:05:01,000 --> 01:05:05,000
He said he's glad you're not around anymore.

393
01:05:20,000 --> 01:05:24,000
Well then...
Tell him this:

394
01:05:35,000 --> 01:05:39,000
I really...

395
01:06:56,000 --> 01:06:59,000
Something burst...

396
01:06:59,000 --> 01:07:03,000
...inside me.

397
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:23,000
I'm sorry about before.

398
01:07:32,000 --> 01:07:36,000
Want some black tea?

399
01:07:53,000 --> 01:07:57,000
Juice.

400
01:08:01,000 --> 01:08:05,000
Wait here, OK?

401
01:08:40,000 --> 01:08:44,000
No matter how much she might have yelled earlier,
she was no match for me.

402
01:08:52,000 --> 01:08:56,000
Will you go ask your mom
about tomorrow?

403
01:09:28,000 --> 01:09:32,000
What? Is something wrong?

404
01:10:16,000 --> 01:10:20,000
Dad's world and mom's world were starting
to become separate from eachother.

405
01:11:06,000 --> 01:11:09,000
What's wrong?

406
01:11:09,000 --> 01:11:13,000
I've become unable to see you together.

407
01:11:14,000 --> 01:11:18,000
You and mom...

408
01:11:18,000 --> 01:11:22,000
Why can't I see the both of you?

409
01:11:25,000 --> 01:11:27,000
What do you mean?

410
01:11:27,000 --> 01:11:31,000
I'm not able to see both you and mom.

411
01:11:36,000 --> 01:11:40,000
Come over here.

412
01:11:53,000 --> 01:11:57,000
That's not how it is.

413
01:12:01,000 --> 01:12:05,000
I'm sorry.

414
01:12:53,000 --> 01:12:57,000
Listen... mom...

415
01:12:58,000 --> 01:13:02,000
Do you remember what you always used to say?

416
01:13:02,000 --> 01:13:05,000
What's that?

417
01:13:05,000 --> 01:13:09,000
"From now on, it's just the two of us,
so let's do our best".

418
01:13:16,000 --> 01:13:19,000
I remember.

419
01:13:19,000 --> 01:13:23,000
I...

420
01:13:25,000 --> 01:13:29,000
I want to live in your world, mom.

421
01:13:49,000 --> 01:13:53,000
After that, I became unable to see dad.

422
01:14:15,000 --> 01:14:19,000
You say your father passed away in a car accident?

423
01:14:27,000 --> 01:14:31,000
Well then, who's that standing
right behind you?

424
01:14:58,000 --> 01:15:02,000
There is nobody there.

425
01:15:10,000 --> 01:15:14,000
It seems he's become unable to see his father.

426
01:15:17,000 --> 01:15:21,000
He can hear my wife's voice, but it
seems he can't hear mine.

427
01:15:23,000 --> 01:15:27,000
If he takes his hand, it seems he simply can't feel it,
even if his mind's used to it.

428
01:15:31,000 --> 01:15:35,000
When I try to hug him, he just becomes like a doll.

429
01:15:47,000 --> 01:15:51,000
So basically...

430
01:15:51,000 --> 01:15:55,000
The two of you were quarreling.

431
01:15:55,000 --> 01:15:59,000
And you both created a world in
which your partner had died.

432
01:16:00,000 --> 01:16:04,000
Living with you lead your child
into believing in that world.

433
01:16:04,000 --> 01:16:08,000
And he became like this.

434
01:16:08,000 --> 01:16:12,000
That's about right, isn't it?

435
01:16:23,000 --> 01:16:27,000
Mom and dad weren't in an accident.

436
01:16:29,000 --> 01:16:33,000
It's sad that I became unable to see dad but...

437
01:16:39,000 --> 01:16:43,000
I definetely think it was for the best.

438
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:39,000
Because I really wanted mom and dad
to be together again.

439
01:18:27,000 --> 01:18:31,000
"Poem of collected sunlight"

440
01:18:52,000 --> 01:18:56,000
Good morning.

441
01:18:56,000 --> 01:19:00,000
- Who are you?
- I'm the human who created you.

442
01:19:04,000 --> 01:19:08,000
- Stand up.
- Yes.

443
01:19:08,000 --> 01:19:12,000
- Follow me, please.
- Yes.

444
01:19:31,000 --> 01:19:35,000
Happy birthday.

445
01:19:45,000 --> 01:19:47,000
Is that the sun?

446
01:19:47,000 --> 01:19:51,000
Exposure to sunlight, even a small
amount has made my temperature rise.

447
01:19:52,000 --> 01:19:56,000
Let's go.

448
01:19:57,000 --> 01:20:01,000
The house in that forest down there...

449
01:20:01,000 --> 01:20:05,000
That's where you'll keep me company.

450
01:20:26,000 --> 01:20:28,000
Come inside.

451
01:20:28,000 --> 01:20:31,000
First, I'd like you to make coffee.

452
01:20:31,000 --> 01:20:34,000
I know what coffee is,
but I don't know how it's made.

453
01:20:34,000 --> 01:20:38,000
That's right, isn't it.

454
01:20:48,000 --> 01:20:51,000
Now, let's drink.

455
01:20:51,000 --> 01:20:55,000
I've memorized how it's made,
so from now on I'll make it.

456
01:20:56,000 --> 01:20:58,000
How was it?

457
01:20:58,000 --> 01:21:00,000
I hate this flavor.

458
01:21:00,000 --> 01:21:04,000
That's good. I made you that way.

459
01:21:07,000 --> 01:21:11,000
Now drink it.

460
01:21:11,000 --> 01:21:14,000
The sweet taste made it easier to drink.

461
01:21:14,000 --> 01:21:18,000
It allows the coffee to be
normally absorbed inside my body.

462
01:21:33,000 --> 01:21:37,000
The people in that picture,
where are they now?

463
01:21:37,000 --> 01:21:41,000
Thery're not anywhere anymore.

464
01:21:58,000 --> 01:22:02,000
What are you going to do with that?

465
01:22:05,000 --> 01:22:09,000
I want you to learn gardening.

466
01:22:26,000 --> 01:22:28,000
- Thanks for the food.
- Thanks for the food.

467
01:22:28,000 --> 01:22:32,000
- It's delicious, but maybe a bit too salty.
- I understand.

468
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:36,000
Do you know what this is?

469
01:22:36,000 --> 01:22:39,000
A rabbit did it.

470
01:22:39,000 --> 01:22:42,000
Then that's what I saw this morning.

471
01:22:42,000 --> 01:22:46,000
But knowing it's been at our food
gives me an unpleasant feeling.

472
01:24:15,000 --> 01:24:19,000
In 47300032000~ seconds...

473
01:24:20,000 --> 01:24:23,000
I will become inactive.

474
01:24:23,000 --> 01:24:27,000
In time, every living thing will,
without fail, become inactive.

475
01:24:46,000 --> 01:24:50,000
That's a beautiful sound. The wind makes it.
It's coincidental music, isn't it.

476
01:24:52,000 --> 01:24:56,000
I like this kind of sound.

477
01:24:58,000 --> 01:24:59,000
3.

478
01:24:59,000 --> 01:25:00,000
2.

479
01:25:00,000 --> 01:25:02,000
1.

480
01:25:02,000 --> 01:25:06,000
It's been exactly one month since I was born.

481
01:25:10,000 --> 01:25:14,000
After one more week,
I will die.

482
01:25:15,000 --> 01:25:18,000
After I die, I want to
be buried on the hill.

483
01:25:18,000 --> 01:25:22,000
I made you for that reason.

484
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:26,000
I understand.

485
01:25:36,000 --> 01:25:40,000
Not again...

486
01:26:21,000 --> 01:26:23,000
Where did you break?

487
01:26:23,000 --> 01:26:27,000
You're still warm.

488
01:26:27,000 --> 01:26:31,000
Thats right!
That man will fix you!

489
01:27:12,000 --> 01:27:15,000
What's wrong?
What on earth happened?

490
01:27:15,000 --> 01:27:18,000
Please fix it.

491
01:27:18,000 --> 01:27:19,000
Please fix this child.

492
01:27:19,000 --> 01:27:23,000
It's already dead.

493
01:27:24,000 --> 01:27:28,000
You're in bad shape.
Let's hurry back to safety.

494
01:27:36,000 --> 01:27:40,000
I... loved this child.

495
01:27:45,000 --> 01:27:49,000
That... is death.

496
01:27:58,000 --> 01:28:02,000
I'm sorry.

497
01:28:04,000 --> 01:28:08,000
I resent you.

498
01:28:08,000 --> 01:28:11,000
Why did you create me?

499
01:28:11,000 --> 01:28:14,000
I...

500
01:28:14,000 --> 01:28:18,000
...I don't want to have to bury
you after you're dead. It's painful!

501
01:28:31,000 --> 01:28:35,000
There are birds' nests in the trees here,
so it won't be lonely.

502
01:28:40,000 --> 01:28:44,000
I will die tomorrow afternoon.

503
01:29:00,000 --> 01:29:02,000
How much time do you have left?

504
01:29:02,000 --> 01:29:06,000
1729 seconds.

505
01:29:06,000 --> 01:29:10,000
I also know exactly how much
time I have left to breathe.

506
01:29:11,000 --> 01:29:15,000
And... you too...

507
01:29:15,000 --> 01:29:19,000
When I fell off the cliff...

508
01:29:19,000 --> 01:29:23,000
I saw the forest's true shape.

509
01:29:28,000 --> 01:29:32,000
There haven't been any humans
here for a long, long time, have there?

510
01:29:37,000 --> 01:29:41,000
For how long have you been alone?

511
01:29:41,000 --> 01:29:44,000
I was made 150 years ago.

512
01:29:44,000 --> 01:29:48,000
The girl who made me, was created by
someone before those 150 years.

513
01:29:50,000 --> 01:29:53,000
By someone who also
had been created by someone.

514
01:29:53,000 --> 01:29:57,000
Then human beings were no more again
for a long time.

515
01:29:58,000 --> 01:30:02,000
But to make you was my dying wish.

516
01:30:02,000 --> 01:30:06,000
Because I thought you'd be very
happy to be born into this world.

517
01:30:12,000 --> 01:30:16,000
Thank you!
